  "local_port": 52650,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which is the best android phone above 35000?",
  "response": "Choosing the \"best\" Android phone above \u20b935,000 (assuming Indian Rupees) depends on your specific needs, such as camera quality, performance, display, battery life, and additional features like stylus support or gaming capabilities. As of October 2023, here are some of the top Android smartphones in the \u20b935,000 and above range:\n\n### 1. **Samsung Galaxy S23 Series**\n- **Models**: Galaxy S23, S23+, S23 Ultra\n- **Key Features**:\n  - **Display**: Dynamic AMOLED 2X, 120Hz refresh rate\n  - **Processor**: Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen 2 (or Exynos, depending on region)\n  - **Camera**: Advanced multi-lens systems, high-resolution sensors (especially in Ultra)\n  - **Battery**: Varies by model, typically 3900mAh to 5000mAh\n  - **Special Features**: S Pen support (Ultra), robust ecosystem, top-tier build quality\n- **Pros**: Excellent performance, outstanding camera quality, premium build\n- **Cons**: Expensive, some features may be region-specific\n\n### 2. **Google Pixel 7 Pro**\n- **Key Features**:\n  - **Display**: 6.7-inch LTPO OLED, 120Hz\n  - **Processor**: Google Tensor G2\n  - **Camera**: Exceptional computational photography, versatile lens setup\n  - **Battery**: Approximately 5000mAh with fast charging\n  - **Software**: Pure Android experience with timely updates\n- **Pros**: Best-in-class camera performance, clean software, regular updates\n- **Cons**: Limited availability in some regions, battery life could be better for heavy users\n\n### 3. **OnePlus 11 Pro**\n- **Key Features**:\n  - **Display**: 6.7-inch Fluid AMOLED, 120Hz\n  - **Processor**: Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen 2\n  - **Camera**: Hasselblad-tuned cameras for natural color calibration\n  - **Battery**: 5000mAh with SuperVOOC fast charging\n  - **Special Features**: OxygenOS with a smooth and customizable user interface\n- **Pros**: Fast performance, excellent display, strong charging capabilities\n- **Cons**: Availability might be limited in some regions, camera performance is good but not class-leading\n\n### 4. **Xiaomi 13 Pro**\n- **Key Features**:\n  - **Display**: 6.73-inch AMOLED, 120Hz\n  - **Processor**: Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen 2\n  - **Camera**: Leica-branded camera system with advanced photography features\n  - **Battery**: 4820mAh with 90W wired and wireless charging\n  - **Special Features**: High build quality, MIUI enhancements\n- **Pros**: Excellent camera system, fast charging, premium design\n- **Cons**: MIUI can have bloatware, software updates may not be as timely as stock Android\n\n### 5. **Sony Xperia 1 V**\n- **Key Features**:\n  - **Display**: 6.5-inch 4K OLED, 120Hz\n  - **Processor**: Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen 2\n  - **Camera**: Triple lens with professional-grade controls, 4K video recording\n  - **Battery**: Approximately 5000mAh\n  - **Special Features**: High-resolution display ideal for media consumption and creation\n- **Pros**: Outstanding display quality, robust video and photography tools\n- **Cons**: Expensive, average battery life compared to peers\n\n### 6. **ASUS ROG Phone 7**\n- **Key Features**:\n  - **Display**: 6.78-inch AMOLED, 144Hz refresh rate\n  - **Processor**: Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen 2\n  - **Camera**: Versatile camera setup, optimized for gaming needs\n  - **Battery**: 6000mAh with fast charging\n  - **Special Features**: Gaming-centric features like AirTrigger buttons, enhanced cooling\n- **Pros**: Superior gaming performance, long-lasting battery, high-refresh-rate display\n- **Cons**: Bulkier design, less focus on camera quality compared to flagship peers\n\n### 7. **Vivo X90 Pro+**\n- **Key Features**:\n  - **Display**: 6.78-inch AMOLED, 120Hz\n  - **Processor**: Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen 2\n  - **Camera**: Zeiss optics, high-resolution sensors, advanced image processing\n  - **Battery**: 5000mAh with fast charging\n  - **Special Features**: Sleek design, impressive photography capabilities\n- **Pros**: Excellent camera performance, premium design, strong performance\n- **Cons**: MIUI-based interface may not appeal to all, limited availability in some regions\n\n### 8. **OPPO Find X6 Pro**\n- **Key Features**:\n  - **Display**: 6.82-inch AMOLED, 120Hz\n  - **Processor**: Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen 2\n  - **Camera**: Leica collaboration with versatile lenses and high-quality imaging\n  - **Battery**: 5000mAh with SuperVOOC fast charging\n  - **Special Features**: Sleek design, innovative cooling solutions\n- **Pros**: Strong camera system, premium build, fast charging\n- **Cons**: Software can be bloated, high price point\n\n### **Key Considerations When Choosing the Best Android Phone Above \u20b935,000:**\n\n1. **Performance**: Look for devices with the latest processors (e.g., Snapdragon 8 Gen 2) and ample RAM (8GB or more) to ensure smooth multitasking and future-proofing.\n2. **Display**: High-refresh-rate AMOLED displays (120Hz or higher) offer better visuals and smoother interactions.\n3. **Camera Quality**: If photography is a priority, consider phones with advanced camera systems and features like optical image stabilization, high megapixel counts, and versatile lens setups.\n4. **Battery Life and Charging**: A sizable battery (4500mAh and above) with fast charging capabilities can enhance usability.\n5. **Software Experience**: Pure Android or well-optimized skins like OxygenOS or One UI can provide a better user experience with timely updates.\n6. **Build Quality and Design**: Premium materials and thoughtful design contribute to durability and aesthetics.\n7. **Special Features**: Features like S-Pen support, gaming enhancements, or superior audio quality might be important based on your use case.\n\n### **Final Recommendation:**\n\nIf you prioritize **camera quality and a pure Android experience**, the **Google Pixel 7 Pro** is an excellent choice. For those seeking a **balanced flagship with robust features and a premium build**, the **Samsung Galaxy S23 Ultra** or **OnePlus 11 Pro** are top contenders. If **gaming performance** is your main focus, the **ASUS ROG Phone 7** stands out. Evaluate your specific needs and preferences to choose the device that best aligns with your requirements.\n\n---\n\n*Please note that availability, pricing, and specific configurations may vary based on your region. It's advisable to check the latest reviews and local prices before making a purchase.*",
